Package org.atlanmod.commons.io.serializer

Interface BinarySerializer<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of (de)serialized objects
    All Superinterfaces:
    Converter<T,​byte[]>, Function<T,​byte[]>, Serializable, Serializer<T,​byte[]>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBinarySerializer
    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public interface BinarySerializer<T>
extends Serializer<T,​byte[]>, Serializable
    An object that is responsible of Object to byte[] encoding and decoding.

      • serialize

        void serialize​(T t,
               @WillNotClose
               OutputStream os)
        throws IOException
        Write an object of type T to the given os.

        If the os also implements DataOutput, prefer using serialize(Object, DataOutput). This method will create a adapter on os before calling it.

        Parameters:
        t - the object to serialize
        os - the output stream
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs during the serialization
